# BFSI Auth

Full spec: `skills/skills_auth.md`. Secure storage: `skills/skills_data_storage.md`.

## Rules

- Tokens: `FlutterSecureStorage` + `AppConstants` keys only — never Hive/SharedPreferences/globals
- `AuthInterceptor`: Bearer on requests; **one** silent refresh on 401, then `clearAll()`
- `go_router` redirect guard is the auth enforcement point (public: login, forgot-password only)
- Roles: enforce in **usecase** (`UnauthorizedFailure`) — never UI-only
- Logout: revoke (best-effort) → `clearAll()` → clear caches → reset Riverpod — never skip `clearAll()`
- Forgot password: always show success (no user enumeration)
- MPIN: SHA-256 + salt; 4–6 digits; lock after 3 failures; never log

## Examples

```dart
// Logout — step 2 is mandatory
try { await _remoteDataSource.logout(); } catch (_) {}
await _storage.clearAll();
await _cacheService.clearAll();
state = const AuthState();

// Role gate in usecase
if (currentUser.role != roleAdmin) {
  return const Left(UnauthorizedFailure());
}
```

## Login (validate in UI first)

Email required + format; password required, min 6 chars. `LoginUsecase` → `Either<Failure, UserEntity>`.

## Do NOT

Log passwords/tokens/MPINs/OTPs · retry refresh more than once · bypass route guard · biometric-only auth
